com.gedder.gedderalarm.model

Class AlarmClock

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.gedder.gedderalarm.model.AlarmClock
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    android.os.Parcelable

    public class AlarmClock
extends java.lang.Object
implements android.os.Parcelable
    An alarm clock class encapsulating all data for both a typical alarm clock and the specialized Gedder alarm clock.

        public AlarmClock(java.lang.String origin,
                  java.lang.String destination,
                  DaysOfWeek repeatDays,
                  java.util.Calendar alarmTime,
                  java.util.Calendar arrivalTime,
                  int prepHour,
                  int prepMinute,
                  java.util.Calendar upperBoundTime)
        A copy constructor with explicit variables.
        Parameters:
        origin - The place the user is leaving from.
        destination - The place the user wants to get to.
        repeatDays - The days this alarm clock will repeat.
        alarmTime - The time for which this alarm is set (or going to be set for).
        arrivalTime - The time the user needs to get to their destination.
        prepHour - The hour portion of the time it takes the user to get prepared for travel after the alarm goes off.
        prepMinute - The minute portion of the time it takes the user to get prepared for travel after the alarm goes off.
        upperBoundTime - The user selected alarm time. If Gedder is activated, this may differ from the actual alarm time.

        public void toggleGedder()

      • turnOn

        public void turnOn()
        Sets a new alarm clock through intents to the Android OS. AlarmReceiver will receive this intent. If the Gedder alarm is also required, tells the GedderAlarmManager to set up the Gedder services for this particular alarm.

      • turnOff

        public void turnOff()
        Cancels any alarm associated with this alarm clock instance. Also terminates any associations with any Gedder services. NOTE: Does not reset alarm data; only cancels the alarm.
